<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>The <link linkend="_struct_leap_1_1_matrix">Matrix</link> struct represents a transformation matrix. </para>



<para>To use this struct to transform a <link linkend="_struct_leap_1_1_vector">Vector</link>, construct a matrix containing the desired transformation and then use the Matrix::transformPoint() or <link linkend="_struct_leap_1_1_matrix_1a64110864a06e02eb50977596633d39a6">Matrix.TransformDirection()</link> functions to apply the transform.</para>

<para>Transforms can be combined by multiplying two or more transform matrices using the * operator. <formalpara><title>Since: </title>

<para>1.0 </para>
</formalpara>
</para>
